{"id":"SR-QUOTE-0001","type":"example_sentence","prompt":"Silk Roads (Quote)","level":"Y7","answer":"For more than two millennia, news and information, goods and products, ideas and beliefs have flowed through networks linking the Pacific coast of China with the Atlantic coast of Europe, crossing the Indian Ocean and the Persian Gulf with the Mediterranean and Central Asia with the 19th century. These networks have been known as the Silk Roads.","tiles":["For","more","than","two","millennia,","news","and","information,","goods","and","products,","ideas","and","beliefs","have","flowed","through","networks","linking","the","Pacific","coast","of","China","with","the","Atlantic","coast","of","Europe,","crossing","the","Indian","Ocean","and","the","Persian","Gulf","with","the","Mediterranean","and","Central","Asia","with","the","19th","century.","These","networks","have","been","known","as","the","Silk","Roads."]}
